    A low-risk project is usually the best way to start.
  </p>

  <p>
    You can still grow tomatoes,
    peppers,
    and other exciting crops.
    Just avoid making your entire first season depend on one slow,
    timing-sensitive plant.
  </p>

  <p class="muted">
    Fast crops build confidence while timing-sensitive crops teach planning.
  </p>
</section>

